        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Farnborough Kent</placeName>
                    <date>Sept. 12<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.—</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>The woodcut<ref target="#foot.f1"/> will now, I think, do very well: but please observe &amp; <hi rend="underline">take steps to rectify</hi> two errors in the spelling of the names of valves.—  for upper lateral read <hi rend="underline">Upper</hi> capital L <hi rend="underline">Latus</hi> for cardinal read <hi rend="underline">Carinal</hi> </p>
<p>Please direct all 4 blocks to be cut close for type.</p>
<p>I suppose it will not signify, but I wrote to M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Bowerbank<ref target="#foot.f2"/> for instructions who sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. cut the block &amp; suggested to him to leave it in your hands, to get done, &amp; then the drawing &amp; cutting w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> be one charge: if any difficulty arises, I will let you hear.—</p>
<p>Though you had to pay only 1<hi rend="superscript">s</hi>/2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> for the parcel I had an extra shilling to pay for porterage; but you will not have any other parcel to send, for, as I said, I will come up to London to compare the proof-sheets of the Engraved Plates, with the specimens.—</p>
<p>I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> be greatly obliged if you could inform me (when the time comes) as soon as you know on what day I shall have the proof-engravings, so that I may know a few days before hand when I shall have to come to London.—</p>
<p>There will be no use to send a proof of one Plate before all 4 are ready.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>I am truly glad that you are making progress</p>
<p>Yours sincerely | C. Darwin</p>
<p>I must see proofs of woodcuts but the Blocks themselves had better be retained by you.—</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.3 capital L] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi></note>
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n2">3.2 in] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi></note>
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n3">5.1 (when the time comes)] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi></note>
                </div>

        </div>

        

        

